        </div>
        <p style="color: #42474e; line-height: 1.65;">Getting the tool deployed is the easy part. Getting people to actually change how they work is where most rollouts stall and never recover.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card text-center">
        <div style="width: 52px; height: 52px; border-radius: 50%; background: rgba(0,37,59,0.08); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="w-6 h-6" stroke="#00253b" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4M12 16h.01"/></svg>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #42474e; line-height: 1.65;">When AI arrives without explanation, people fill the gap with fear. Anxiety about job security kills adoption before it has any chance to take hold.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #e7eeff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; max-width: 680px; margin: 2.5rem auto 0; text-align: center;">
      <p style="color: #00253b; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">For the record: our goal is the opposite.</p>
      <p style="color: #42474e; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0;">We train your team to use AI as a tool that makes them better at their jobs. Not faster at getting fired. Every workshop we run starts with this: AI is here to help you do more, not to replace you.</p>
    </div>
    <p style="color: #006875; text-align: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.125rem; margin-top: 2rem;">Our workshops solve all three: hands-on, role-specific, and tailored to your industry.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── PROGRAMS ── -->
