      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── WHAT EACH ROLE LEARNS ── -->
<section class="section" style="background: #f0f3ff;" aria-labelledby="roles-heading">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 id="roles-heading">What Each Role Actually Learns</h2>
      <p style="color:#42474e; font-size:1.0625rem;">Training only sticks when it maps to someone's real workday. Pick a role to see the kind of tasks we train on. Every exercise uses scenarios from your own business, not textbook examples.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="role-tabs" data-role-tabs>
      <div class="tab-buttons" role="tablist" aria-label="Team role">
        <button type="button" class="tab-btn active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-tab="sales">Sales</button>
        <button type="button" class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="ops">Operations</button>
        <button type="button" class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="hr">HR</button>
        <button type="button" class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="marketing">Marketing</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="sales">
        <div class="role-item"><span class="role-num">1</span><p><strong>Prospect research in minutes:</strong> pull together a company's recent news, key people, and likely pain points before a call, instead of skimming their website in the car park.</p></div>
        <div class="role-item"><span class="role-num">2</span><p><strong>Follow-ups in your own voice:</strong> draft personalized follow-up emails that sound like you wrote them, referencing what was actually discussed.</p></div>
